SIMPLE: sinewy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinewy
<hw>Sin"ew*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to, consisting of, or resembling, a sinew or
sinews.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>sinewy</qex> thread my brain lets fall.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Well braced with, or as if with, sinews; nervous;
vigorous; strong; firm; tough; <as>as, the <ex>sinewy</ex>
Ajax</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A man whose words . . . were so close and <qex>sinewy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinful</ent>⟦br⟧
